            "headline": "Global empty capsules market expected to reach USD 4.61 billion by 2034, growing at a CAGR of 5.26% with sales of approx. USD 2.98 billion in 2025.",
            "id": "7b385ad8-01c7-47aa-aec0-bf3014213a0d",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "The global Empty Capsules Market is expected to grow significantly, with the market size valued at around USD 2.76 Billion in 2024, reaching USD 2.98 Billion in 2025, and projected to hit approximately USD 4.61 Billion by 2034 at a CAGR of 5.26%. This growth is driven by factors such as the rising demand for pharmaceuticals, ease of ingestion, and higher bioavailability compared to oral tablets. Gelatin capsules held the majority market share in 2024 at 73.5%, with North America leading with 34.7% market share. Non-gelatin capsules, especially popular in vegetarian and vegan products, are expected to grow at a fast pace. The report covers market trends, size, segmentation by type, functionality, application, and region, with a forecast period from 2025 to 2034.",
