            "is_major": false,
            "source": "GlobeNewswire",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "Recently acquired by HI-VIEW RESOURCES INC., a company based in Vancouver, British Columbia, are two separate mineral claim applications adjacent to Quebec Innovative Materials Corp. (CSE: QIMC). The company plans to conduct a Phase 1 work program and data compilation on these highly prospective mineral claim packages. These blocks are situated within the Timiscaming Graben formation, about 15 km north of Ville Marie, Quebec, in close proximity to a hydrogen sample discovery by Quebec Innovative Materials Corp. where levels exceeded 1,000 ppm, as declared on September 4th, 2024. Accessible by road (Route 101), the mineral claim applications hold significant potential and are strategically located between two major mining cities. HI-VIEW is listed as CSE: HVW; OTCQB: HVWRF; FSE: B63.",
